        {\mathrm{Re} \,}f((1-\epsilon)e^{it}) \geq \frac{1}{\epsilon}\mu(t-\epsilon,t+\epsilon)$$ for any $t$ and $\epsilon>0$ small. Together with the Jitomirskaya-Last inequality of the CMV version (see Section 10.8 of ), we have $$\label{eq.measControl}
        \mu(t-\epsilon,t+\epsilon)<C \epsilon\sup_{0\leq s\leq c\epsilon^{-1}}\Vert T^{s}_{e^{it}}\Vert^{2}.$$

