Let $z=\cos2\pi a\in[-1,1]$, our goal is to obtain the estimate: $$\sum_{j\in I_{1}\cup I_{2},j\neq i}\left(\log |\cos2\pi a-\cos2\pi\theta_{j}|-\log|\cos2\pi\theta_{i}-\cos2\pi\theta_{j}|\right)<3sq_{m}\epsilon$$ for any $i$. Denote $$S_{1}=\sum\limits_{j\in I_{1}\cup I_{2},j\neq i}\log|\cos2\pi a-\cos2\pi\theta_{j}|+3s(q_{m}-1)\log 2$$ and $$S_{2}=\sum\limits_{j\in I_{1}\cup I_{2},j\neq i}\log|\cos2\pi\theta_{i}-\cos2\pi\theta_{j}|+3s(q_{m}-1)\log 2.$$ By a trigonometric identity, $$S_{1}=\left(\sum\limits_{j\in I_{1}\cup I_{2},j\neq i}\log|\sin\pi(a+\theta_{j})|+\log|\sin\pi(a-\theta_{j})|\right)+(3sq_{m}-1)\log2.$$ Note that the sum in $S_{1}$ contains $3sq_{m}$ terms, which we can divide it into $3s$ groups, each of which contains $q_{m}$ terms and then apply Lemma <a href="#lem.AJ09" data-reference-type="ref" data-reference="lem.AJ09">36</a>. We have the following: $$\label{eq.estS1}S_{1}\leq -3s(q_{m}-1)\log2+3sC\log q_{m}.$$ Similarly, we can write $$S_{2}=\left(\sum\limits_{j\in I_{1}\cup I_{2},j\neq i}\log|\sin\pi(2\theta+(i+j)2\Phi)|+\log|\sin\pi(i-j)2\Phi|\right)+3s(q_{m}-1)\log2.$$

Since $\Phi\in{\mathrm{DC}}(\kappa,\tau)$, for any $0<|j|< q_{m+1}$, we have $$\Vert j2\Phi\Vert_{{\mathbb{T}}}\geq \Vert q_{m}2\Phi\Vert_{{\mathbb{T}}}\geq\frac{\kappa}{(2q_{m})^{\tau}},$$ which implies that $$\label{eq.dioEq1}\max\{\log|\sin\pi x|,\log|\sin\pi(x+j2\Phi)|\}\geq 2\log\kappa-2\tau\log 2q_{m}.$$ Since $\theta$ is non-resonant with respect to $\Phi$, we have $$\label{eq.dioEq2}
            \log|\sin2\pi(\theta+(i+j)\Phi)|\geq -|i+j|^{\frac{1}{2\tau}}\geq -(20sq_{m})^{\frac{1}{2\tau}},$$ and since $\Phi\in{\mathrm{DC}}(\kappa,\tau)$, we also have $$\label{eq.dioEq3}
            \log|\sin\pi(i-j)2\Phi|\geq \log\kappa-\tau\log20sq_{m}.$$ By <a href="#eq.dioEq1" data-reference-type="eqref" data-reference="eq.dioEq1">[eq.dioEq1]</a>, every $sq_{m}$ terms in the sum of $S_{2}$ may contain at most one extra small term that is bounded from below by <a href="#eq.dioEq2" data-reference-type="eqref" data-reference="eq.dioEq2">[eq.dioEq2]</a> and <a href="#eq.dioEq3" data-reference-type="eqref" data-reference="eq.dioEq3">[eq.dioEq3]</a>.

